** Your role **

As a Signals Intelligence Analyst in the Air Force, you’ll play an important
role in turning electronic codes and radar signals into intelligence that
supports exercises, operations, and missions. You’ll use cutting-edge
electronic warfare technology and software to draw on highly classified
material and reverse engineer complex signals into useful information.

** Your duties may include: **

  * Manipulating large volumes of data to map new and historical intelligence to a particular platform (e.g. aircraft). 
  * Identifying and correlating other forms of intelligence and reporting to enhance confidence levels in existing intelligence. 
  * Providing timely briefs and reporting to deployed ADF and allied platforms. 
  * Identifying unusual activity. 
  * Analysing technical intelligence to identify radars, and their capabilities and functions. 

You’ll be paid from day one to gain all the skills needed with extensive on-
the-job training, all while living an adventurous lifestyle and making a
difference to Australia.

** Benefits **

  * Competitive salary package 
  * Generous superannuation 
  * Good work/life balance 
  * Career progression and development 
  * Supportive team environment 
  * Free medical and dental 
  * Job security 
  * Travel opportunities 

** **

** Salary **

Upon completion of initial military and employment training, you will enjoy a
salary package starting from $79,555.

** Location **

Following training, you may be posted to one of the major Air Force bases
around Australia, such as RAAF Base Amberley, Williamtown, or Edinburgh.

** Apply Now: **

Apply today and we’ll get in contact with you shortly.

For this role, you must be at least 17 at the time of enlistment, an
Australian Citizen, and have passed in Year 10 English, Science (with a
Physics component) and Intermediate Maths.

Visit the link below for the full position description and detailed
application requirements.

